      <text>Guildees,

I just wanted to touch upon a few issues, so please forgive me if I
begin to ramble.

OOC vs. IC:
The guild channels are OOC. What is said in tells is OOC. What I say
to you oocly is OOC. Are you getting the drift of it? Now what does 
this mean to you? It means that if we are discussing an RP situation 
that you are involved in, things brought up in the OOC conversation
that we are having should not be used to effect your IC situation. 
Granted, sometimes I might need things done on a case by case basis,
but I will be -very-, -very-, clear when I am making this kind of a 
request on you.

The DL syllabus:
For those of you non-DLs, the post is over unless you are just
curious as to what is going to be said. It is stated in the syllabus 
that the rules exist but given the nature of Dark RP, rules can sometimes
be broken. This doesn't mean you are automatically in the shit house. 
It just means if you get caught ICly, you are going to be in the IC 
shithouse. Which means what? Go ahead and do it if you think you aren't
going to get caught if you think it will further your machinations. Or
don't do it if you don't want Death or the Mistress of Pain knocking 
on your front door with a basket of balefire for you. 

Flames, comments, questions, etc. can me mudmailed to me or brought
up in tells.

Thanks,
Darith
</text>
