      <authorname>Bayani</authorname>
      <text>It was a quiet mid-morning at the Queen's Blessing as Jadene started her 
daily rounds to the inn's rooms.  She knocked on each door gently to see
if anyone was there.  If not, then she cleaned the room as she does 
everyday about this time. 

As she neared the last door of the hallway, it seemed quieter than usual,
atleast as she looks back on it.  But perhaps that's because she knows 
now what was on the other side of the door.  After no answer to the knock 
on the door, she opened it and took a step inside.  Seconds later, her 
screams reverberated through the hallway and even could be heard down 
in the common room below.  

Hurried footsteps could be heard as the Innkeeper as well as a few others 
rushed to see what was amiss.  With her hand over her mouth, muffling the 
screams that still tore its way from her throat, she pointed with her free hand.  
There, hanging from the rafters of the room, was the body of a young woman.  
Her long, blond hair partially covered the smooth skin of her face, ice blue 
eyes now covered with the veil of death as she swung slowly in the air.  

Her room held little details as to why this girl would kill herself, if in fact it 
was a suicide.  Among her possessions was a sealed letter addressed to a 
man named simply as Erick.
</text>
